article.headline: Alabama St. 70, Auburn-Montgomery 52
article.story: MONTGOMERY, Ala. (AP) -- Chief Kickingstallionsims scored 17 points and Alabama State held Auburn-Montgomery to 29 percent shooting in a 70-52 victory Thursday night. Andrew Hayles added 11 points and eight rebounds and Brandon Books collected 10 points and 10 boards for the Hornets (4-4). They led 31-25 at the half over AUM (9-4), an NAIA school located just a few miles away from Alabama State's campus. The Hornets then shot 57 percent in the second half to pull away. Alabama State dominated the boards 48-36. Joshua Randall led AUM with 16 points, while Quadavious Brown added 12 and Ronnie Hickman had 10.
